    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AppDriver
    Application entry point for the WordTracker program.
    BSTree<E>
    A generic Binary Search Tree (BST) implementation.
    BSTreeADT<E>
    The BSTreeADT interface is designed to be used as a basis for the BST data structure that will be developed in the CPRG304 F2025 class at SAIT.
    BSTreeNode<E>
    A single node within a Binary Search Tree (BST).
    BSTreeTest
     
    Iterator<E>
    This interface will provide an mono-directional iterator for any of the data structures that are specified in this package.
    Utils
     
    Word
    Represents a word stored in the BST and tracks all occurrences of that word across multiple files and line numbers.
    WordTracker
    Manages a repository of Word objects stored inside a BSTree.
